		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The differences isn't always in the functionnement, but sometimes also in the technology used.
<br />I say that, because I noticed MMC1As tend to somewhat overheat, while later MMC1B doesn't have that problem.
<br />Of course I'm not sure at all, but maybe MMC1B use better transistors that draw less current when switching or something like this.
<br />So of course that also applies to MMC3s.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


